Key Match Events: Jurickson Profar made a jumping catch into the crowd to rob a home run in the first inning.
The Dodgers suffered a 10-2 defeat against the Padres.
In the 7th inning, Profar tossed a ball to the crowd, which led to Dodgers fans throwing it back along with other objects, causing the game to be stopped for several minutes.
Post-Match Reflections: In a postgame interview, Jurickson Profar said the situation felt 'dangerous' and compared it to a similar experience with San Francisco Giants fans.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Padres are limiting ticket sales to Dodgers fans for game three and four at Petco Park to maintain home-field advantage.
